"title": "7233: Israel, as northern kingdom",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7233: israel, as northern kingdom",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The northernmost region of the two kingdoms, comprising the ten northern tribes which broke away from Judah in 930 B.C. and remained independent until the Assyrian conquest of 722 B.C., when the nation was exiled because of its sinfulness.</p>\n<h2>Origins of the division between Judah and Israel</h2>\n<h3>Israelite settlement in Canaan had developed around two distinct regions in the north and south</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:5\">JOS 18:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The northern Israelite tribes were less ready to transfer allegiance from Saul to David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:10\">2SA 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:41-2Sam20:2\">2SA 19:41–20:2</a> <em>Israel seems to have been ready to follow Sheba, because he came from the same tribe as Saul.</em></p>\n<h3>Israel's separation from Judah was the result of disobedience under Solomon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:26-1Kgs11:33\">1KI 11:26–11:33</a></p>\n<h3>Rehoboam's folly provoked Israel's rebellion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:1-1Kgs12:17\">1KI 12:1–12:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:1-2Chr10:17\">2CH 10:1–10:17</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's foreign affairs</h2>\n<h3>Israel at war with Judah (c. 930–886 B.C.)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:30\">1KI 14:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:15\">2CH 12:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:2-2Chr13:3\">2CH 13:2–13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:1\">2CH 16:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:16-1Kgs15:17\">1KI 15:16–15:17</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's wars with Aram (c. 886–753 B.C.)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:18-1Kgs15:20\">1KI 15:18–15:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:2-2Chr16:4\">2CH 16:2–16:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:1\">1KI 20:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:26\">1KI 20:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:24-2Kgs6:25\">2KI 6:24–6:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:32-2Kgs10:33\">2KI 10:32–10:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:3\">2KI 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:24-2Kgs13:25\">2KI 13:24–13:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:28\">2KI 14:28</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's alliance with Judah against Aram and Moab (853 B.C.)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:1-1Kgs22:4\">1KI 22:1–22:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:1-2Chr18:3\">2CH 18:1–18:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:4-2Kgs3:7\">2KI 3:4–3:7</a></p>\n<h3>Israel attacked by Assyria (c. 743–734 B.C.)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:19-2Kgs15:20\">2KI 15:19–15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:29\">2KI 15:29</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's alliance with Aram against Judah (c. 735/734 B.C.)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:5\">2KI 16:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:1\">ISA 7:1</a></p>\n<h3>Israel conquered by Assyria, and her inhabitants exiled (722 B.C.)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:3-2Kgs17:6\">2KI 17:3–17:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:9-2Kgs18:11\">2KI 18:9–18:11</a></p>\n<h2>Centres of worship in Israel</h2>\n<h3>The calf idols in Bethel and Dan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:26-1Kgs12:33\">1KI 12:26–12:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:29\">2KI 10:29</a></p>\n<h3>Worship of Baal and Asherah in the capital, Samaria</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:32-1Kgs16:33\">1KI 16:32–16:33</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Gilgal was also a centre of worship</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:11\">HOS 12:11</a></p>\n<h2>Condemnation of Israel's way of life</h2>\n<h3>Israel's worship condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:4-Amos4:5\">AMO 4:4–4:5</a></strong> <em>Amos' language here is full of irony.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:11-Hos8:13\">HOS 8:11–8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:21-Amos5:24\">AMO 5:21–5:24</a></p>\n<h3>The corruption of Israel's priests condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:9\">HOS 6:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:6-Hos4:9\">HOS 4:6–4:9</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's unfaithfulness to God condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:7\">HOS 5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:7-2Kgs17:23\">2KI 17:7–17:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:10-Hos4:13\">HOS 4:10–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Prophetic condemnation of sin in Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:1-Hos4:2\">HOS 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:11-Hos7:2\">HOS 6:11–7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6-Amos2:8\">AMO 2:6–2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:12\">AMO 5:12</a></p>\n<h3>Israel condemned for looking to foreign nations for help instead of to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:12-Hos12:1\">HOS 11:12–12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:13-Hos5:15\">HOS 5:13–5:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:8-Hos7:11\">HOS 7:8–7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:9-Hos8:10\">HOS 8:9–8:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's attitude to the northern kingdom of Israel</h2>\n<h3>God's call to Israel to repent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:1-Hos14:2\">HOS 14:1–14:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:12\">HOS 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:4-Amos5:6\">AMO 5:4–5:6</a></p>\n<h3>God's attempt to call Israel back through hardship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:1\">1KI 17:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:6-Amos4:11\">AMO 4:6–4:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's rejection of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:6\">HOS 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:5-2Chr25:7\">2CH 25:5–25:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:8-Hos1:9\">HOS 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's punishment of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:26-Amos5:27\">AMO 5:26–5:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:5-Hos10:8\">HOS 10:5–10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:11-Amos3:12\">AMO 3:11–3:12</a></p>\n<h3>God's intention to restore Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:10\">HOS 1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:23\">HOS 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:4-Hos14:8\">HOS 14:4–14:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:11-Amos9:15\">AMO 9:11–9:15</a></p>",
